NOTES

Variables are created using '=' with no space before or after

When using arguments, ${@} takes all arguments while ${1...n} takes the said number

${0} returns the name of the file

Arrays are created using (). Indexed using [], where as [@] returns all its elements

prepending with # return the number of elements
      example
        echo ${#arr[@]}


if statements
  if [[ test ]] 
  then
    commands
  fi

if- else statements
  if [[ test ]]
  then
    commands
  else
    commands
  fi  

LOOP




        



